parameters

Class TactileDistractorParameter

  • java.lang.Object
    • parameters.Parameter
      • parameters.TactileDistractorParameter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class TactileDistractorParameter
extends Parameter
    This is a children class of Parameter. It encapsulate the behavior of the tactile distractor during the experiment such as the the duration time of a vibration. The distractor implements a long and a short vibrations.

      • TactileDistractorParameter

        public TactileDistractorParameter(int longVibrationDuration,
                          int shortVibrationDuration,
                          int intervalDuration,
                          int numberOfVibration,
                          EParameterPosition positionInTrial)
        Creates a tactile distractor parameters by providing each attributes a value.
        Parameters:
        longVibrationDuration - Duration in milliseconds of the long vibration.
        shortVibrationDuration - Duration in milliseconds of the short vibration.
        intervalDuration - Duration in milliseconds of the down time between 2 vibrations.
        numberOfVibration - Number of vibrations to happen during a trial.
        positionInTrial - List of all the parameters affecting the experiment.
        See Also:
        m_longVibrationDuration, m_shortVibrationDuration, m_intervalDuration, m_numberOfVibrations, Parameter.m_positionInTrial
